L(/login/)` should pass.\n\nThe `emailInput` selector is `input[name=\"email\"][type=\"email\"]`. Let me check if the actual element has `name=\"email\"`. From the snapshot, it's a textbox with placeholder \"abc@gmail.com\". Let me check the actual HTML.\n\nFor TC-83238, the snapshot at this login page shows there's ALSO a newsletter email input at the bottom! So the homepage newsletter IS there on this page too! That confirms the selector issue - the login page also has a newsletter section. But the test navigates to the HOME page first.\n\nLooking at the login page snapshot - the URL changed to `/auth/login` on redirect from `/myaccount`. The current LoginPage.ts code:\n```typescript\nawait this.page.goto('/myaccount');\nawait this.page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\nawait this.page.waitForURL(/login/, { timeout: 20_000 }).catch(() => {});\nawait this.emailInput.waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 45_000 });\n```\n\nThe redirect goes to `/auth/login` which contains `/login`. The `waitForURL` SHOULD fire at this point. Then `emailInput.waitFor` - the input is visible. This should work!\n\nUnless the issue is that the redirect happens BEFORE `waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')` completes, and then the URL check passes but the page isn't fully loaded yet. But actually `waitForURL` waits for the URL to be the target, not for the page to load.\n\n**Key issue for TC-83240**: The error-context shows OLD LoginPage code (15s timeout) which was already fixed to 45s. This failure is from an OLDER run. The current code should handle it.\n\nBut wait - I should check if the email input actually has `name=\"email\"`. Let me check the HTML.\n\nAlso, the reCAPTCHA is interesting. If the reCAPTCHA is required, the login will NEVER succeed in automation without special handling (like test mode or mocking).\n\nLet me check the login page HTML for the email input attributes.\n"}}
