RL(\n    (url) => !url.pathname.includes('/myaccount/login') && !url.pathname.includes('/login'),\n    { timeout: 30_000 },\n);\n```\n\nWait - `/auth/login` CONTAINS '/login'. So the success URL check `!url.pathname.includes('/login')` would FAIL for `/auth/login`. The `waitForURL` would wait until the URL changes to something WITHOUT '/login' in it. After successful login, it redirects to `/myaccount` or `/` which doesn't contain '/login'. That makes sense.\n\nBut with reCAPTCHA... the login click would be intercepted and the URL would never change. So the `waitForURL` would timeout after 30s.\n\nThis means TC-83240 would fail with a DIFFERENT error now (URL timeout, not email input timeout). The error shown is from the OLD code.\n\nOK, so the actual situation:\n- TC-83232: Newsletter - ACTUALLY FAILING (confirmed current code has the issue)  \n- TC-83240: Wishlist login - Was failing with old code (email input timeout). Current code has 45s timeout for email input, but login will STILL fail due to reCAPTCHA → URL wait timeout.\n- TC-83238: In-store pickup (firefox/webkit) - Was failing with old code. Current code has dual-link fallback.\n\nFor TC-83238, I should verify the current code works. The store selector fallback should handle both cases.\n\nFor TC-83240, the reCAPTCHA is a problem. But maybe the UAT environment has reCAPTCHA in test mode (always passes). Since 78 tests passed and some of those might be authenticated... Actually no, TC-83240 IS one of the failing tests.\n\nLet me look at what the test does again. The test needs to login to test the wishlist. If reCAPTCHA always blocks, this test fundamentally can't work. Maybe in UAT, reCAPTCHA is disabled or uses test keys.\n\nActually, looking at the test - it was probably working before (or was recently added as a test that needs reCAPTCHA bypass). The Additional Instructions say to fix the failures. \n\nFor TC-83240, the fix needs to handle the fact that:\n1. Email input timeout (old issue) - already fixed\n2. reCAPTCHA - may or may not be bypassed in UAT\n\nSince I can see the reCAPTCHA on the page, and the test was listed as failing, maybe the login page structure recently changed. \n\nLet me check if there's any cookie storage auth approach or if there's a way to bypass the login.\n\nActually, looking at the playwright.config.ts - there's no `storageState` setup for authenticated tests. So each test that needs auth does the full login flow.\n\nFor TC-83240, the most pragmatic fix without reCAPTCHA bypass is to:\n1. Navigate directly to the login page URL (`/auth/login`) instead of `/myaccount`\n2. The email input wait is already at 45s\n3. Hope that reCAPTCHA is in test mode on UAT\n\nOR mark TC-83240 as `.skip()` pending reCAPTCHA resolution. But the user wants it fixed, not skipped.\n\nActually - the reCAPTCHA might be solvable. In UAT environments, sometimes reCAPTCHA uses TEST keys that always pass. Let me just try to interact with it and see.\n\nWait - I see the reCAPTCHA \"No soy un robot\" (Spanish - that's weird for London Drugs). This might be a test reCAPTCHA that actually works in automation.\n\nFor now, let me focus on the definitive fixes:\n\n**Fix 1 - TC-83232 (Newsletter, all browsers):**\n- In `tests/home-page.spec.ts`: Increase `networkidle` timeout from 10s to 30s; increase retry loop from 8×800ms to 15×1000ms; increase final `waitFor` from 30s to 45s\n- In `pages/HomePage.ts`: Keep selector but also try `input[placeholder=\"Enter your email\"]` as alternative\n\n**Fix 2 - TC-83240 (Login/Wishlist):**\n- In `pages/LoginPage.ts`: Navigate directly to `/auth/login` instead of `/myaccount` to avoid redirect delay\n- Keep the 45s timeout (already fixed)\n- Add a `waitForLoadState('networkidle')` after navigation\n\n**Fix 3 - TC-83238 (In-Store Pickup, firefox/webkit):**\n- Current code already has the dual-link fallback. Verify it's correct.\n- The fallback waits 5s for \"Set your store\" then tries \"Check Availability\". This should work.\n- Maybe increase the `waitForTimeout` from 1500ms to 2500ms for firefox/webkit to allow more time to hydrate\n\nLet me now implement these fixes.\n"}}
